      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions - Improvements to consider] Line 116: The multiplicative decrease factor is computed as `1.0f - congestion * maxDecreaseFactor`, which means `maxDecreaseFactor\u003d0.5` produces only a 5% reduction at congestion\u003d0.1, despite the comment saying factor\u003d0.95. The following `max()` is redundant and makes the naming ambiguous. This can make congestion response too weak or hard to tune. Use an explicit minimum factor or rename the config to reflect the actual semantics.\n```suggestion\n    const float minFactor \u003d 1.0f - cfg_.maxDecreaseFactor;\n    float factor \u003d std::clamp(1.0f - congestion * cfg_.maxDecreaseFactor, minFactor, 1.0f);\n```",
