      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions - Improvements to consider] Line 253: Audio congestion reduction uses hard-coded factors 0.45 and 0.55, bypassing the configurable `audioReductionFactor`. This makes tuning inconsistent and also differs from the previous 0.4/0.5 severe-loss behavior removed from VideoRtpSession. Consider making these severity factors part of Config or deriving them from `audioReductionFactor` so deployments can tune audio protection coherently.\n```suggestion\n    float reductionFactor \u003d cfg_.audioReductionFactor;\n    if (audioLoss \u003e 10.0f)\n        reductionFactor \u003d std::min(reductionFactor, 0.45f);\n    else if (audioLoss \u003e 5.0f)\n        reductionFactor \u003d std::min(reductionFactor, 0.55f);\n```",
