      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions - Improvements to consider] Line 663: RTT is fed as `rtcpi.latency` without validating whether the field is available or in milliseconds. If latency is unset or uses a sentinel/invalid value, it can establish a bogus baselineRtt_ in the first five samples and permanently skew congestion scoring for the call. Validate the value before passing it to the controller, or pass 0 when no RTT sample is available.\n```suggestion\n                const float rttMs \u003d rtcpi.latency \u003e 0 ? rtcpi.latency : 0.0f;\n                auto newBitrate \u003d bwController_.update(rtcpi.packetLoss,\n                                                       static_cast\u003cfloat\u003e(rtcpi.jitter),\n                                                       rttMs);\n```",
